I will, I will.

721
00:43:35,760 --> 00:43:39,218
[Screaming]

722
00:43:39,297 --> 00:43:42,824
Mommy, Mommy, let me out!

723
00:43:42,900 --> 00:43:47,234
[Screaming]
No! Mommy!

724
00:43:47,305 --> 00:43:50,274
Mommy, don't leave me!

725
00:43:50,341 --> 00:43:52,832
I'm not going anyplace, honey.
We're gonna stay here.

726
00:43:52,910 --> 00:43:55,504
- Let me handle this.
- [Screaming Continues]

727
00:43:55,579 --> 00:43:59,140
- Here. You know what?
- Mommy!

728
00:43:59,216 --> 00:44:02,185
- [Crying]
- You know what we're gonna do
when you get better?

729
00:44:02,253 --> 00:44:04,346
We're gonna go
to the playroom.

730
00:44:04,422 --> 00:44:06,982
- Mommy, don't leave me!
- They have some neat toys in there.

731
00:44:07,058 --> 00:44:09,322
And when you get
really, really better...

732
00:44:09,393 --> 00:44:12,328
-we're gonna go down to the cafeteria...
-Mommy!

733
00:44:12,396 --> 00:44:16,162
- and we're gonna get
some lemon merengue pie.
- Mommy!

734
00:44:16,233 --> 00:44:18,997
- [Crying Continues]
- It's the best.

735
00:44:19,070 --> 00:44:23,166
[Sobbing]
Oh, I can't. I just can't.

736
00:44:23,240 --> 00:44:26,505
- It's okay.
- Mommy, Mommy, let me out, please!

737
00:44:26,577 --> 00:44:29,341
- It's gonna be okay.
- Help me!

738
00:44:29,413 --> 00:44:32,644
- [Sobbing Continues]
- Please let me out!

739
00:44:49,433 --> 00:44:51,526
[Man On P.A.]
Dr. Abbasac, code blue.

740
00:44:51,602 --> 00:44:55,732
[Alarm Beeping]
Dr. Abbasac, code blue.
Dr. Abbasac, code blue.

741
00:45:03,614 --> 00:45:05,946
- Good morning.
- [Woman] Good morning, Steve.

742
00:45:10,187 --> 00:45:13,850
Ohhh! Oh!

743
00:45:16,160 --> 00:45:19,220
[Phone Ringing,
Machines Beeping]

744
00:45:19,296 --> 00:45:22,231
[People Chattering,
Children Crying]

745
00:45:30,241 --> 00:45:32,801
- He has a fever.
- How high?

746
00:45:32,877 --> 00:45:35,710
- We've stabilized it.
- Oh.

747
00:45:35,780 --> 00:45:38,715
[Panting]
Why does he have a fever?

748
00:45:38,783 --> 00:45:41,911
It could be an infection. It could
be part of the seizure disorder.

749
00:45:41,986 --> 00:45:43,920
It could be the medication.

750
00:45:43,988 --> 00:45:47,355
That's something you're gonna have to
talk to Dr. Abbasac about.

751
00:45:52,830 --> 00:45:54,798
That a boy.
You're okay.

752
00:45:54,865 --> 00:45:57,231
Where is Lili?

753
00:45:57,301 --> 00:46:00,862
[Stammers]
The little girl in the other bed.

754
00:46:00,938 --> 00:46:03,304
What happened to her?

755
00:46:04,809 --> 00:46:07,539
- She's dead, isn't she?
- It's extremely rare.

756
00:46:07,611 --> 00:46:09,909
She died of the epilepsy,
not the surgery.

757
00:46:09,980 --> 00:46:13,939
There's something wrong here.
There's something really,
really, really wrong!

758
00:46:14,018 --> 00:46:18,352
I bring my kid to you people
for help, and all you do
is make him sicker.

759
00:46:18,422 --> 00:46:22,825
You give him one drug,
and then he needs another drug
to cure him of the first one.

760
00:46:22,893 --> 00:46:26,829
And then he needs another drug
to take away the side effects
of that one!

761
00:46:26,897 --> 00:46:29,491
And another one and another one
and another one-- I mean, he--

762
00:46:29,567 --> 00:46:32,331
He has had a rash,
swollen glands, a fever...

763
00:46:32,403 --> 00:46:35,668
...constipation, hemorrhoids,
bleeding gums--

764
00:46:35,739 --> 00:46:39,470
And he acts like a drunk,
a zombie, a psycho.

765
00:46:39,543 --> 00:46:43,946
And it's not because of his sickness.
It's because of your cure.

766
00:46:44,014 --> 00:46:48,041
If Robbie doesn't get better...

767
00:46:48,119 --> 00:46:52,579
...if he ends up in a home, strapped
to a wheelchair somewhere, huh...

768
00:46:52,656 --> 00:46:54,749
...what are you
gonna tell me then?

769
00:46:54,825 --> 00:46:58,022
That it's all some big
idiopathic tragedy?

770
00:46:58,095 --> 00:47:00,290
- Lori.
- I'm sorry.

771
00:47:00,364 --> 00:47:03,822
But, you know, there must be
something else that you can do.
There must be something.

772
00:47:03,901 --> 00:47:06,699
Lori, wait.
I've been meaning to give this
to you for your signature.

773
00:47:06,770 --> 00:47:09,432
It's the paperwork on
the compassionate use program.

774
00:47:09,507 --> 00:47:12,032
We want to try
an experimental drug.

775
00:47:12,109 --> 00:47:14,669
[Woman On P.A.]
Dr. Abbasac, code blue.

776
00:47:14,745 --> 00:47:19,512
Dr. Abbasac, code blue.
Dr. Abbasac, code blue.

777
00:47:21,519 --> 00:47:24,352
[Gasping, Choking]

778
00:47:27,057 --> 00:47:30,254
[Chattering]

779
00:47:30,327 --> 00:47:33,455
He's in status.
Two milligrams, Valium IV.

780
00:47:33,531 --> 00:47:36,796
[Robbie Continues Gasping]

781
00:47:38,235 --> 00:47:40,703
One more.

782
00:47:40,771 --> 00:47:45,105
[Robbie Gasping]
Help me! Help!

783
00:47:45,176 --> 00:47:48,009
[Machine Beeping]

784
00:47:48,078 --> 00:47:52,037
Another milligram Valium IV.
Repeat until we have cessation.

785
00:47:52,116 --> 00:47:55,108
[Gasping Continues]

786
00:47:55,186 --> 00:47:57,245
[Beeping Continues]

787
00:47:57,321 --> 00:47:59,414
Get me four milligrams
paraldehyde.

788
00:47:59,490 --> 00:48:02,516
Hurry. He's
in status epilepticus.

789
00:48:02,593 --> 00:48:05,061
If we can't stop it, we risk
permanent brain damage.

790
00:48:05,129 --> 00:48:09,691
Paraldehyde is a drug that
temporarily freezes the nervous
system and prevents that.

791
00:48:09,767 --> 00:48:12,327
- But like any drug,
it carries its own risks.
- What risks?

792
00:48:12,403 --> 00:48:16,499
Depressing the nervous system
can result in pulmonary edema,
even death.

793
00:48:16,574 --> 00:48:21,375
That's the choice? Probable
brain damage or possible death?

794
00:48:21,445 --> 00:48:24,505
Paraldehyde.

795
00:48:26,417 --> 00:48:30,046
Not oral. Miss Warren, get me a
rectal syringe for the paraldehyde.

796
00:48:30,120 --> 00:48:33,180
But not plastic.

797
00:48:33,257 --> 00:48:35,589
Miss Warren.

798
00:48:37,027 --> 00:48:39,621
Get me four more milligrams
paraldehyde.

799
00:48:39,697 --> 00:48:42,598
[Machine Continues Beeping]

800
00:48:46,704 --> 00:48:48,763
[Man]
Paraldehyde.

801
00:48:48,839 --> 00:48:51,535
[Dr. Abbasac]
Turn him on his side.

802
00:48:51,609 --> 00:48:54,043
[Robbie Crying]

803
