00:57:48,605 --> 00:57:52,507
#gonna be somewhere#

926
00:57:52,576 --> 00:57:56,535
#over the rainbow#

927
00:57:56,613 --> 00:58:01,380
#Oh#

928
00:58:01,451 --> 00:58:05,854
#where pretty little
bluebirds fly#

929
00:58:05,922 --> 00:58:09,824
#birds fly#

930
00:58:09,893 --> 00:58:13,852
#all over the rainbow#

931
00:58:13,930 --> 00:58:16,524
#Why#

932
00:58:16,600 --> 00:58:20,400
#then, oh, why#

933
00:58:20,470 --> 00:58:29,401
#can't I?#

934
00:58:33,683 --> 00:58:36,049
[Phone Rings]

935
00:58:38,088 --> 00:58:40,556
What's goin'on?

936
00:58:40,624 --> 00:58:43,149
- It's Mom.
- Is Robbie worse?

937
00:58:43,226 --> 00:58:47,492
No, he's the same. She said
she found something, um--

938
00:58:47,564 --> 00:58:51,933
Different kind of treatment
that could help Robbie. A diet.

939
00:58:52,002 --> 00:58:54,095
You mean it can make
his seizures go away?

940
00:58:54,171 --> 00:58:57,732
Good, Mom. A diet.
Why don't we try a rain dance?

941
00:58:57,808 --> 00:59:01,300
Then I'll get a doll
that we can all stick pins in.

942
00:59:01,378 --> 00:59:04,074
[Phone Rings]

943
00:59:05,282 --> 00:59:08,251
Dr. Forman's office.
How may I help you?

944
00:59:08,318 --> 00:59:10,411
Hi, this is Lori Reimuller...

945
00:59:10,487 --> 00:59:14,685
...and I've just read, uh,
Dr. Livingston's book about the diet...

946
00:59:14,758 --> 00:59:19,195
...that treats childhood epilepsy,
and I would like to make
an appointment for my son.

947
00:59:19,262 --> 00:59:22,629
Well, we have a cancellation
tomorrow at 1:30.

948
00:59:22,699 --> 00:59:26,726
But you're, uh, in Maryland, and
I'm calling from Kansas City.

949
00:59:26,803 --> 00:59:30,330
I'm sorry. Well, that's our
only opening for three months.

950
00:59:30,407 --> 00:59:33,171
Three months?
Oh, no, no, no, no, no. [Sighs]

951
00:59:33,243 --> 00:59:35,177
Robbie can't wait three months.
He's too sick.

952
00:59:35,245 --> 00:59:38,772
Well, then he'll require hospitalization,
and there are no available beds...

953
00:59:38,849 --> 00:59:42,478
...in our inpatient program
for the foreseeable future.

954
00:59:42,552 --> 00:59:46,352
Uh, why don't I put you on our
waiting list. We do have cancellations.

955
00:59:46,423 --> 00:59:51,588
- I need to talk to the doctor.
- He's with patients, Mrs. Reimuller.

956
00:59:51,661 --> 00:59:56,064
Why don't you send us your son's
records. I'm sure something
will come up before too long.

957
00:59:56,132 --> 00:59:58,600
Okay, I'll take that
appointment tomorrow.

958
00:59:58,668 --> 01:00:01,637
- What is the patient's name?
- Uh, Robbie...

959
01:00:01,705 --> 01:00:04,173
...Reimuller. R-e-i...

960
01:00:04,241 --> 01:00:07,142
- Excuse me.
- ...m-u-l-l-e-r.

961
01:00:07,210 --> 01:00:10,611
- Thank you.
- Who is it?

962
01:00:15,819 --> 01:00:18,515
I've-- I've been doing
some reading, and I've...

963
01:00:18,588 --> 01:00:22,115
...come across a treatment
for epilepsy...

964
01:00:22,192 --> 01:00:25,992
...called the keto--
ketogenic diet.

965
01:00:26,062 --> 01:00:28,826
It's by a doctor
from Johns Hopkins.

966
01:00:28,899 --> 01:00:31,891
And the diet,
the best I understand it...

967
01:00:31,968 --> 01:00:35,529
...makes the body go into a fasting
state, and something about that
fasting state...

968
01:00:35,605 --> 01:00:38,005
...stops the seizures.

969
01:00:38,074 --> 01:00:42,374
The Comprehensive Management
of Epilepsy in Infancy,
Childhood and Adolescence...

970
01:00:42,445 --> 01:00:44,379
...by Samuel Livingston.

971
01:00:44,447 --> 01:00:48,747
The bible on pediatric epilepsy.
Every neurologist in the country
owns a copy.

972
01:00:48,818 --> 01:00:51,753
With the exception
of the material on the ketogenic diet...

973
01:00:51,821 --> 01:00:54,449
...it's an invaluable piece
of medical literature.

974
01:00:54,524 --> 01:00:57,049
The diet is not
an approved treatment.

975
01:00:57,127 --> 01:01:00,221
- But there have been a lot of studies.
- Those studies are anecdotal...

976
01:01:00,297 --> 01:01:04,495
...not the kind of studies we base
sound medical judgement on,
not double-blind studies.

977
01:01:04,567 --> 01:01:06,728
The ketogenic diet
is highly suspect.

978
01:01:06,803 --> 01:01:10,967
You have to starve the child
to begin with, and what you
feed him consists mainly of fat...

979
01:01:11,041 --> 01:01:15,068
...which is not only unpalatable
but nutritionally inadequate and
extremely difficult to maintain.

980
01:01:15,145 --> 01:01:18,410
I've seen it tried a few times,
and my experience is that
it simply doesn't work.

981
01:01:18,481 --> 01:01:21,279
I've been meaning
to give this to you.

982
01:01:21,351 --> 01:01:25,720
It's the number of an outstanding
pediatric neurosurgeon on our staff.

983
01:01:25,789 --> 01:01:27,984
It's time to see
if we can find a focus...

984
01:01:28,058 --> 01:01:30,652
...a starting point in the brain
for Robbie's seizures.

985
01:01:30,727 --> 01:01:34,754
If we can, there's
a good possibility we can remove it.

986
01:01:34,831 --> 01:01:36,856
Not brain surgery.
We don't want brain surgery.

987
01:01:36,933 --> 01:01:40,369
I'm not proposing surgery.
Not yet.

988
01:01:40,437 --> 01:01:42,462
I'm talking about
a diagnostic procedure.

989
01:01:42,539 --> 01:01:46,066
We remove the top of the skull
and place electrodes
on the brain for a few days...

990
01:01:46,142 --> 01:01:49,373
...to see if we can map it
and try and locate the problem.

991
01:01:49,446 --> 01:01:54,748
It's the next logical step, and
I'd like to schedule it immediately.

992
01:01:54,818 --> 01:01:59,152
We can't because
we're goin' to Baltimore.

993
01:01:59,222 --> 01:02:04,353
Robbie has an appointment with
Dr. Forman at Johns Hopkins tomorrow.

994
01:02:04,427 --> 01:02:06,019
And how are you planning
to get Robbie to this appointment?

995
01:02:06,096 --> 01:02:08,894
I booked us on a flight.

996
01:02:08,965 --> 01:02:13,299
There is a danger of
a life-threatening seizure
if you stop the drugs abruptly.

997
01:02:13,370 --> 01:02:15,895
Well, who's talking about
stopping drugs?

998
01:02:15,972 --> 01:02:21,410
I, uh, have administered enough
drugs to Robbie in nine months
to get a pharmacy degree.

999
01:02:29,686 --> 01:02:33,679
You'll need an ambulance
to transfer him from the hospital...

1000
01:02:33,757 --> 01:02:37,693
...a plane that will accommodate
a medical transfer, his meds...

1001
01:02:37,761 --> 01:02:43,666
...a drip, emergency oxygen
and a doctor to accompany him.

1002
01:02:43,733 --> 01:02:46,759
There is no way
that we can afford all that.

1003
01:02:49,873 --> 01:02:54,401
When you have met these conditions
for his safe transport...

1004
01:02:54,477 --> 01:02:57,412
...I'll be glad to sign
for his release.

1005
01:03:06,790 --> 01:03:10,226
[People Chattering,
Machine Beeping]

1006
01:03:47,931 --> 01:03:50,866
- [Moans]
- Shh, shh, shh.

1007
01:04:02,378 --> 01:04:05,313
- Have you taken his B.P.?
- Yeah, I did.

1008
01:04:24,701 --> 01:04:26,635
Oh!

1009
01:04:26,703 --> 01:04:31,697
-Can I help you?
-Radiology, um-- My son needs an X ray.

1010
01:04:31,774 --> 01:04:34,868
- Let me see your lab slip.
I'll tell you where to go.
- Oh, huh--

1011
01:04:34,944 --> 01:04:39,176
I must've left that
down in emergency.

1012
01:04:39,249 --> 01:04:41,547
Take the elevator
to the first floor, follow the signs.

1013
01:04:41,618 --> 01:04:44,553
Okay, thanks.

1014
01:04:54,864 --> 01:04:56,991
Major babe.

1015
01:05:28,198 --> 01:05:30,257
Ma'am?

1016
01:05:31,868 --> 01:05:34,428
Ma'am.

1017
01:05:42,378 --> 01:05:44,312
Security.

1018
01:06:01,497 --> 01:06:03,692
Ma'am?
Ma'am, excuse me.

1019
01:06:03,766 --> 01:06:06,599
You'll have to come with me.

1020
01:06:08,671 --> 01:06:11,606
[Machine Beeping,
People Chattering]

1021
01:06:19,415 --> 01:06:22,646
Do you know what would have happened
if he hadn't stopped you?

1022
01:06:22,719 --> 01:06:25,916
Yeah, I'd be on a plane
to Baltimore.

1023
01:06:27,857 --> 01:06:31,486
When he was discovered missing, an all
points bulletin would have gone out.

1024
01:06:31,561 --> 01:06:34,553
- What? My arrest?
- Yes.

1025
01:06:34,631 --> 01:06:36,690
- I was the mother.
- It doesn't matter.

1026
01:06:36,766 --> 01:06:39,098
You could have been charged with
kidnapping and child endangerment.

1027
01:06:39,168 --> 01:06:42,399
- You could've lost custody.
- What?

1028
01:06:42,472 --> 01:06:45,236
The institution can petition
for legal guardianship of any child...

1029
01:06:45,308 --> 01:06:49,404
...whose interest and well-being they feel
aren't being served by his parents.

1030
01:06:49,479 --> 01:06:51,811
And the courts
usually grant it.

1031
01:06:51,881 --> 01:06:56,011
Well, what if I feel that
his interests are not being
served by the institution?

1032
01:06:56,085 --> 01:07:00,613
What if I feel that he's,
he's actually being harmed
by the whole, you know, system?

1033
01:07:00,690 --> 01:07:06,026
What if-- What if I just can't sit here
and watch him... fade away?

1034
01:07:06,095 --> 01:07:08,893
Don't I have a right?
Don't I?

1035
01:07:08,965 --> 01:07:12,128
- To try to protect my own child?
- Lis-- I--

1036
01:07:12,201 --> 01:07:17,935
I shouldn't be telling you this.
I could get in a lot of trouble.

1037
01:07:18,007 --> 01:07:20,373
We had a staff meeting
this afternoon.

1038
01:07:20,443 --> 01:07:24,038
Dr. Abbasac discussed your plans
to take Robbie to Baltimore.

1039
01:07:24,113 --> 01:07:27,844
She believes you're losing it,
that your judgement's impaired.

1040
01:07:27,917 --> 01:07:30,613
- And after tonight they have
all the evidence they need--
- Oh, they're not--

1041
01:07:30,687 --> 01:07:33,121
they're not talkin' about
takin' Robbie away from me.

1042
01:07:33,189 --> 01:07:38,126
She's on her way down here now.
It might be best if you were
gone when she gets here.

1043
01:07:43,399 --> 01:07:45,333
All right.

1044
01:07:47,203 --> 01:07:51,003
I don't agree with the doctor.
I think you know your child
better than any of us...

1045
01:07:51,074 --> 01:07:55,443
...and you're just trying to do
what's right for him.

1046
01:07:55,511 --> 01:07:59,311
A lot of kids get well here...

1047
01:07:59,382 --> 01:08:02,146
...but Robbie's not.

1048
01:08:20,536 --> 01:08:22,470
[Schwartz Snorts]

1049
01:08:29,278 --> 01:08:32,076
- Oh. Come on!
- [Whinnies]

1050
01:08:47,897 --> 01:08:52,391
[Screams]

1051
01:09:00,643 --> 01:09:05,046
So even though we missed
the appointment, I went back
and looked it up again.

1052
01:09:05,114 --> 01:09:07,742
And all these doctors
had the same results.

1053
01:09:07,817 --> 01:09:13,050
About a third of the kids
that stick with the diet
have their seizures go away.

1054
01:09:13,122 --> 01:09:17,183
And another third are
significantly improved. Look.

1055
01:09:17,260 --> 01:09:21,458
1927. Dr. Hemholtz
from the Mayo Clinic.

1056
01:09:21,531 --> 01:09:23,897
Uh, 1937.

1057
01:09:23,966 --> 01:09:28,369
That's Dr. Wilkins
from Johns Hopkins.

1058
01:09:28,438 --> 01:09:31,896
And-- And--
And 1954, 1973.

1059
01:09:31,974 --> 01:09:34,841
Dr. Livingston
from Hopkins.

1060
01:09:34,911 --> 01:09:38,608
And 1963, Dr. Keith
from the Mayo Clinic.

1061
01:09:38,681 --> 01:09:43,675
And 1989, and-- We're talking
a couple thousand kids, here.

1062
01:09:43,753 --> 01:09:47,154
And-And look, look.
Just last year.

1063
01:09:47,223 --> 01:09:50,590
Published 1992.
Johns Hopkins.

1064
01:09:50,660 --> 01:09:56,326
They took 58 of the sickest kids,
put them on the ketogenic diet...

1065
01:09:56,399 --> 01:10:00,426
...and almost a third of'em
had their seizures go away.

1066
01:10:00,503 --> 01:10:05,736
The 1920s? How many kids like Robbie
have there been since then?

1067
01:10:05,808 --> 01:10:08,902
I mean, how many children
have been given drugs and operated on...

1068
01:10:08,978 --> 01:10:11,378
...and not one of them
was told of this diet?

1069
01:10:11,447 --> 01:10:13,381
Something doesn't make sense.

1070
01:10:13,449 --> 01:10:17,078
I mean, if all the doctors
we've talked to know
about this "kenogenic" diet--

1071
01:10:17,153 --> 01:10:19,986
- Ketogenic.
- Ketogenic diet.

1072
01:10:20,056 --> 01:10:23,753
Even if they don't like it
for some reason, don't they
have to tell us about it?

1073
01:10:23,826 --> 01:10:26,624
Can they really censor
information like this?

1074
01:10:26,696 --> 01:10:31,258
How can there be joint decision
making if they don't give us
information, tell us options?

1075
01:10:31,334 --> 01:10:33,268
Didn't you say Doc Peterson...

1076
01:10:33,336 --> 01:10:36,237
talked with
his neurologist friends about Robbie...

1077
01:10:36,305 --> 01:10:39,103
...and not one of them
mentioned a diet?

1078
01:10:39,175 --> 01:10:41,439
That's right.

1079
01:10:41,511 --> 01:10:43,979
Just drugs... and surgery.

1080
01:10:44,046 --> 01:10:47,948
If this stands any chance
of working, let alone...

1081
01:10:48,017 --> 01:10:52,420
...a one in three chance
of stopping his seizures altogether...

1082
01:10:54,524 --> 01:10:58,119
...why would they rob us
of that hope?

1083
01:11:02,698 --> 01:11:04,632
[Phone Rings]

1084
01:11:08,004 --> 01:11:09,938
Dave Reimuller.

1085
01:11:16,479 --> 01:11:19,471
We'll be there.

1086
01:11:19,549 --> 01:11:23,007
Meeting with Abbasac in an hour. She
wants to talk about Robbie's surgery.

1087
01:11:23,085 --> 01:11:26,782
- Oh.
- Uh.

1088
01:11:26,856 --> 01:11:29,950
I'll, uh, I'll meet you.

1089
01:11:30,026 --> 01:11:32,085
Don't see anyone
until I get there.

1090
01:11:32,161 --> 01:11:34,629
I'll meet you in an hour.

1091
01:11:40,069 --> 01:11:42,003
[Sighs]

1092
01:11:42,138 --> 01:11:44,003
[People Chattering]

1093
01:11:53,716 --> 01:11:55,650
Doc?

1094
01:11:55,718 --> 01:12:01,623
Hi. Dave tells me I might
be of some help to you.

1095
01:12:01,691 --> 01:12:03,682
[Knocking]

1096
01:12:03,759 --> 01:12:06,387
Come in.

1097
01:12:11,033 --> 01:12:13,729
- There's no need to have
an attorney present.
- I'm not a lawyer.

1098
01:12:13,803 --> 01:12:17,261
- I'm a friend of the family.
- This is Jim Peterson. Dr. Abbasac.

1099
01:12:17,340 --> 01:12:20,571
This is Dr. Alison,
the pediatric neurosurgeon
I mentioned to Lori.

1100
01:12:20,643 --> 01:12:23,806
- How do you do?
- Hi.

1101
01:12:23,879 --> 01:12:26,677
Please sit down.

1102
01:12:26,749 --> 01:12:31,345
I examined Robbie this morning
and, uh, reviewed his record.

1103
01:12:31,420 --> 01:12:34,651
We have his procedure
scheduled for tomorrow morning.

1104
01:12:34,724 --> 01:12:38,353
I'll just need the signed
consent form I gave you
so we can process the paperwork.

1105
01:12:40,997 --> 01:12:43,431
The Reimullers have decided
to go in another direction.

1106
01:12:43,499 --> 01:12:47,959
They're gonna enroll their child
in the ketogenic diet program
at Johns Hopkins.

1107
01:12:49,905 --> 01:12:53,204
I told Lori what conditions
for safe transfer must be met...

1108
01:12:53,275 --> 01:12:56,335
...including a medical doctor
to accompany Robbie.

1109
01:12:56,412 --> 01:12:58,471
Now, I don't know
of a single M.D. who would endorse...

1110
01:12:58,547 --> 01:13:01,778
...the kind of foolishness she's
proposing to subject her son to.

1111
01:13:01,851 --> 01:13:04,718
Of course you don't.
Since so many in our profession...

1112
01:13:04,787 --> 01:13:07,449
...choose not to look beyond
the limits of drugs and surgery.

1113
01:13:07,523 --> 01:13:11,323
It's what made me change careers, but
I've kept my medical license current.

1114
01:13:11,394 --> 01:13:15,592
- You're a physician?
- We'll meet your conditions
for Robbie's safe transfer.

1115
01:13:15,665 --> 01:13:18,133
I'll accompany him
to Baltimore.

1116
01:13:20,803 --> 01:13:25,035
I assume you've spoken to Johns Hopkins
about these arrangements?

1117
01:13:26,409 --> 01:13:29,970
I have, and the arrangements
have been made.

1118
01:13:30,046 --> 01:13:32,310
They're expecting us.

1119
01:13:32,381 --> 01:13:35,373
Dr. Peterson?

1120
01:13:35,451 --> 01:13:39,717
I assume you know
all the evidence in favor of
the ketogenic diet is anecdotal.

1121
01:13:39,789 --> 01:13:42,883
There is absolutely
no scientific evidence this diet works.

1122
01:13:42,958 --> 01:13:47,657
When you say scientific evidence,
if you mean double-blind studies...

1123
01:13:47,730 --> 01:13:50,198
...then I have to ask you,
where are the double-blind
studies on the effects...

1124
01:13:50,266 --> 01:13:53,758
...of the interactions between all
the drugs you've had Robbie on?

1125
01:13:53,836 --> 01:13:55,997
Where are the studies
on the surgery you'll propose...

1126
01:13:56,072 --> 01:13:58,632
...as a result
of the electrocorticogram?

1127
01:13:58,708 --> 01:14:04,578
Dr. Abbasac, to arbitrarily
pretend that your treatments
for epilepsy are science...

1128
01:14:04,647 --> 01:14:06,638
...and then argue against
a ketogenic diet...

1129
01:14:06,716 --> 01:14:10,345
...seems to me to be the cruelest
of double standards.

1130
01:14:10,419 --> 01:14:14,822
When you and I became doctors,
we swore an oath that said,
"First do no harm. "

1131
01:14:14,890 --> 01:14:17,723
Now, if these folks wanna try
to control their son's seizures...

1132
01:14:17,793 --> 01:14:20,694
...by changing what he eats
instead of drugs and surgery...

1133
01:14:20,763 --> 01:14:23,664
...well, I think
they deserve that chance.

1134
01:14:31,674 --> 01:14:36,270
Dr. Abbasac gave the order
to pull him off the paraldehyde...

1135
01:14:36,345 --> 01:14:39,280
...to prevent respiratory problems
while he's traveling.

1136
01:14:39,348 --> 01:14:43,785
Hopefully there'll still
be enough left in his blood
to keep him from seizing.

1137
01:14:45,688 --> 01:14:50,057
I put in for a couple
of vacation days, and my supervisor's...

1138
01:14:50,126 --> 01:14:52,560
...pulling together the meds
he'll need for the trip.

1139
01:14:52,628 --> 01:14:56,826
You're goin' with us, then?

1140
01:14:56,899 --> 01:15:02,303
Things don't fall into place
the way this has-- Dr. Peterson
offering to go with you...

1141
01:15:02,371 --> 01:15:05,670
...another space opening up
for Robbie at Hopkins--

1142
01:15:05,741 --> 01:15:09,040
unless they're meant to be.

1143
01:15:09,111 --> 01:15:14,549
Besides, I think Dr. Peterson
is volunteering his degree,
not his expertise.

1144
01:15:14,617 --> 01:15:16,847
If something should go wrong,
he'd need me.

1145
01:15:16,919 --> 01:15:20,446
I haven't seen a doctor
insert an IV in 15 years.

1146
01:15:20,523 --> 01:15:22,991
[Laughs]

1147
01:15:28,197 --> 01:15:30,188
- Heads up.
- Hey.

1148
01:15:30,266 --> 01:15:33,133
Found a place for you
to stay... free!

1149
01:15:33,202 --> 01:15:35,966
Wh-- Holy Sisters
of Saint Francis?

1150
01:15:36,038 --> 01:15:38,336
Mmm! My sister
was a novice there.

1151
01:15:38,407 --> 01:15:42,503
She says the nuns are very nice,
even though they don't talk.

1152
01:15:42,578 --> 01:15:45,672
- Uh! Mom in a silent convent?
- [Laughs]

1153
01:15:45,748 --> 01:15:49,149
Well, it could happen.

1154
01:15:51,220 --> 01:15:54,986
Come on, buddy.
Whoa!

1155
01:15:55,057 --> 01:15:58,026
We're goin' on an airplane,
you know that?

1156
01:15:58,093 --> 01:16:01,790
Big, big, big one.

1157
01:16:05,434 --> 01:16:08,597
I'm excited, Mommy.

1158
01:16:12,107 --> 01:16:16,737
You know that I believe in my bones
what you're doing is wrong.

1159
01:16:16,812 --> 01:16:19,246
I know you do.

1160
01:16:21,317 --> 01:16:26,311
I've been told over the years that I'm
not the easiest person to deal with.

1161
01:16:28,257 --> 01:16:33,320
I hope you're not sacrificing
this beautiful child to
a personality conflict with me.

1162
01:16:36,332 --> 01:16:40,666
He's my boy, and I'm his mom.
I'm just doing what I think is right.

1163
01:16:42,371 --> 01:16:47,274
If it were your child, can you honestly
say you'd do anything different?

1164
01:16:52,915 --> 01:16:54,849
I'll be sending you
little bird kisses.

1165
01:16:54,917 --> 01:16:56,976
Hope you get to ride
in a jumbo jet.

1166
01:16:57,052 --> 01:16:58,986
Bye, buddy.

1167
01:16:59,054 --> 01:17:01,147
- Bye, Mom.
- Bye, Mom.

1168
01:17:01,223 --> 01:17:03,157
- I'll take care of him.
- Okay.

1169
01:17:03,225 --> 01:17:06,126
- Thanks.
- Be nice to the nuns.

1170
01:17:08,163 --> 01:17:10,097
Be careful.

1171
01:17:16,472 --> 01:17:18,565
- Bye, Robbie.
- Have a good flight!

1172
01:17:21,510 --> 01:17:23,944
Good luck, squirt.

1173
01:17:34,490 --> 01:17:36,549
[Robbie Whimpering]

1174
01:17:36,625 --> 01:17:39,560
- Put this underneath.
- We've arranged for an ambulance.

1175
01:17:41,130 --> 01:17:44,031
- It's okay.
- It's already been 15 minutes.

1176
01:17:44,099 --> 01:17:48,729
- Should we give him
some Valium intramuscularly?
- That's it.

1177
01:17:48,804 --> 01:17:51,568
- He's okay.
- Good. I'll tell the pilot.

1178
01:17:51,640 --> 01:17:54,768
- That's it, sweetie.
- [Sighs]

1179
01:17:54,843 --> 01:17:56,777
[Sighs]

1180
01:17:58,847 --> 01:18:01,407
[Tires Screeching]

1181
01:18:08,257 --> 01:18:10,191
[People Chattering]

1182
01:18:12,294 --> 01:18:14,728
- Hi.
- May I help you?

1183
01:18:14,797 --> 01:18:16,924
I'm-- I'm Lori Reimuller.

1184
01:18:18,567 --> 01:18:23,334
Oh, yes, Mrs. Reimuller.
Your son's appointment was two days ago.

1185
01:18:23,405 --> 01:18:27,671
I know, I know, I know. But, uh, this
was the soonest that we could get here.

1186
01:18:27,743 --> 01:18:31,645
I'm sorry. Don't you remember
I told you very clearly on the phone...

1187
01:18:31,714 --> 01:18:37,448
...we have no appointment openings
with Dr. Forman or available
beds in our hospital program.

1188
01:18:37,519 --> 01:18:42,718
He has to be in the hospital.
He transferred out of pediatric
intensive care to come here.

1189
01:18:43,759 --> 01:18:45,693
Wait here.

1190
01:18:52,968 --> 01:18:55,436
What do we got here?

1191
01:18:55,504 --> 01:18:58,598
Oh! This is Robbie Reimuller.
I'm his mom.

1192
01:18:58,674 --> 01:19:01,666
- Uh, I have his medical records.
- I've seen them.

1193
01:19:01,744 --> 01:19:06,113
As my receptionist told you,
there are no more beds in the clinic.

1194
01:19:06,181 --> 01:19:08,775
Please, you're not gonna tell me
after we've come all this way...

1195
01:19:08,851 --> 01:19:12,844
- ...that we have to turn around
and go... back.
- [Moans]

1196
01:19:17,559 --> 01:19:20,653
It's of the utmost importance
that the ketogenic diet be started...

1197
01:19:20,729 --> 01:19:22,993
...under strict
medical supervision.

1198
01:19:23,065 --> 01:19:26,193
There are risks.
Do you have a place nearby to stay?

1199
01:19:26,268 --> 01:19:28,702
Yes, yes.
Five minutes away.

1200
01:19:28,771 --> 01:19:31,399
No needles. Follow.

1201
01:19:31,473 --> 01:19:33,771
When was his last meal?

1202
01:19:33,842 --> 01:19:35,901
Uh, breakfast, this morning.

1203
01:19:35,978 --> 01:19:38,446
Push.

1204
01:19:38,514 --> 01:19:41,005
All right.
No more food for two days.

1205
01:19:41,083 --> 01:19:43,677
- And then we'll start the diet.
- [Sighs]

1206
01:19:43,752 --> 01:19:47,483
You know, they took him off
paraldehyde to make the trip out here.

1207
01:19:47,556 --> 01:19:51,754
And the place where we're staying isn't
really set up for a sick child.

1208
01:19:51,827 --> 01:19:54,728
He wants to be treated
like a normal healthy boy.

1209
01:19:54,797 --> 01:19:57,857
Do that, starting now.

1210
01:20:00,035 --> 01:20:03,266
I've been on an airplane.

1211
01:20:03,338 --> 01:20:05,670
And how'd you like that?

1212
01:20:05,741 --> 01:20:07,675
Fun.

1213
01:20:07,743 --> 01:20:10,439
[Chuckles]

1214
01:20:10,512 --> 01:20:13,743
[Sighs]

1215
01:20:13,816 --> 01:20:17,946
I'm sorry. I thought he would be
staying in the hospital.

1216
01:20:18,020 --> 01:20:23,117
I wouldn't ask you except that
we don't have anyplace else to go.

1217
01:20:23,192 --> 01:20:27,891
No male has ever
slept on these premises.

1218
01:20:31,700 --> 01:20:36,103
[Sighs] If you can manage
with the simple essentials...

1219
01:20:36,171 --> 01:20:41,131
...you're both welcome to stay
with us as long as you need to.

1220
01:20:41,210 --> 01:20:44,941
- Thank you.
- Sister Josephine
will show you to your room.

1221
01:20:45,013 --> 01:20:47,379
Can I have a minute?

1222
01:20:54,022 --> 01:20:56,855
If, uh, he gets bad,
you be sure and call 911.

1223
01:20:56,925 --> 01:21:01,988
The hospital can always find
a bed on an emergency basis.

1224
01:21:02,064 --> 01:21:06,967
I know "sorry" doesn't
begin to cover it, but--

1225
01:21:08,070 --> 01:21:11,096
You understand
if anything had happened...

1226
01:21:11,173 --> 01:21:15,576
,,,Marissa could've lost
her license and her livelihood.

1227
01:21:17,279 --> 01:21:19,873
[Sighs]

1228
01:21:26,188 --> 01:21:28,679
- Thank you.
- Oh.

1229
01:21:28,757 --> 01:21:33,694
I wonder if you'll ever know
how lucky you are to have
this lady for a mother.

1230
01:21:39,268 --> 01:21:42,032
- There you go, buddy.
- Hey.

1231
01:21:42,104 --> 01:21:44,766
- [Laughs]
- Thanks.

1232
01:21:50,846 --> 01:21:52,780
Okay.

1233
01:22:10,165 --> 01:22:13,464
- Hi.
- Good morning. How's
everything going so far?

1234
01:22:13,535 --> 01:22:17,027
Good! I, um,
I dreaded the fast.

1235
01:22:17,105 --> 01:22:21,166
I thought he'd be beggin'me
for food, but so far he's not.

1236
01:22:21,243 --> 01:22:24,076
He has had... seizures
the last two days...

1237
01:22:24,146 --> 01:22:26,580
...but only small ones.

1238
01:22:26,648 --> 01:22:32,280
I don't know if it's
my imagination or not, but his
whole body seems more relaxed.

1239
01:22:32,354 --> 01:22:36,757
Many parents notice positive changes
during the fasting period.

1240
01:22:36,825 --> 01:22:39,259
Fasting rests the body.

1241
01:22:39,328 --> 01:22:43,162
Now, you'll know within
a month whether the diet
is gonna work for Robbie.

1242
01:22:43,232 --> 01:22:45,962
And if it does, you'll
keep him on it for two to three years...

1243
01:22:46,034 --> 01:22:48,525
...before returning him
to a normal diet.

1244
01:22:48,604 --> 01:22:52,700
- Okay.
- To be effective, the ketogenic diet...

1245
01:22:52,774 --> 01:22:55,607
...must be rigidly controlled.

1246
01:22:55,677 --> 01:22:59,204
Each meal is precalculated, and all
foods are weighed on a gram scale.

1247
01:22:59,281 --> 01:23:02,717
- Right.
- It's difficult.

1248
01:23:02,784 --> 01:23:07,983
Well, is it more difficult
than watchin' your kid have
a hundred seizures a day?

1249
01:23:08,056 --> 01:23:10,650
I've been teaching
and administering the ketogenic diet...

1250
01:23:10,726 --> 01:23:13,718
...here at Hopkins
since 1949...

1251
01:23:13,795 --> 01:23:16,286
...to well over 500 patients.

1252
01:23:16,365 --> 01:23:21,632
I've never seen a parent,
win, lose or draw, that regrets
having given it a try.

1253
01:23:24,806 --> 01:23:27,468
Dear Dave, Lynn and Mark:

1254
01:23:27,542 --> 01:23:31,979
This is day five.
I'm holding my breath.

1255
01:23:32,047 --> 01:23:36,381
No seizures
for three whole days.

1256
01:23:36,451 --> 01:23:38,385
Not one.

1257
01:23:38,453 --> 01:23:42,082
I guess it could be the drugs, but we
already started to take them away.

1258
01:23:42,157 --> 01:23:47,117
The plate is already weighed
and now I'm gonna weigh out 17 grams--

1259
01:23:47,195 --> 01:23:52,724
Mrs. Kelly, the dietician here--
she's been so enthusiastic and helpful.

1260
01:23:52,801 --> 01:23:56,202
She treats us like we were her first
patients. It's hard to believe...

1261
01:23:56,271 --> 01:23:59,331
...she's been doin'this
for over 40 years.

1262
01:23:59,408 --> 01:24:04,004
See how close
to 17 that is? Yeah.

1263
01:24:04,079 --> 01:24:08,072
- I wanna know how good it tastes.
- [Laughs] He loves bacon.

1264
01:24:08,150 --> 01:24:12,416
Robbie's meals are actually
much better looking
than I thought they'd be.

1265
01:24:12,487 --> 01:24:14,421
And he wolfs 'em down.

1266
01:24:14,489 --> 01:24:16,889
[Priest]
Our scripture today is from Matthew 17.

1267
01:24:16,958 --> 01:24:18,926
"A man came to Him
saying, 'Lord..."

1268
01:24:18,994 --> 01:24:22,987
"...have mercy on my son,
for he has epilepsy
and suffers severely'.

1269
01:24:23,065 --> 01:24:25,966
"And Jesus rebuked the demon,
and he came out of him..."

1270
01:24:26,034 --> 01:24:29,026
"...and the child was cured
from that very hour.

1271
01:24:29,104 --> 01:24:31,538
"Then the disciples came
to Jesus privately and said..."

1272
01:24:31,606 --> 01:24:34,006
"...'Why could not
we cast him out?'"

1273
01:24:34,076 --> 01:24:39,844
"And Jesus said, 'This kind does not
go out except by prayer and fasting'."

1274
01:24:39,915 --> 01:24:42,213
Let us pray. Father...

1275
01:24:42,284 --> 01:24:45,378
...we ask Your blessing
on this child, Robbie...

1276
01:24:45,454 --> 01:24:50,016
...that he may come forth from
sickness into health, to live
as Your servant in wholeness--

1277
01:24:50,092 --> 01:24:53,926
[Lori] The nuns are
so good to us. They really
made us feel welcome.

1278
01:24:53,995 --> 01:24:58,932
And we're trying not to disrupt
their lives too much.

1279
01:24:59,000 --> 01:25:05,166
- Roast beef.
- I'm almost afraid to say this,
but I think this is working.

1280
01:25:05,240 --> 01:25:08,767
- Tonight we have a choice of--
- I know it is.

1281
01:25:11,012 --> 01:25:14,243
Dave, I keep remembering
the questions you asked...

1282
01:25:14,316 --> 01:25:16,910
...about the doctors
censoring information...

1283
01:25:16,985 --> 01:25:20,682
...and robbing us
even of hope.

1284
01:25:20,756 --> 01:25:23,691
And I keep wondering, what could
have gone so horribly wrong...

1285
01:25:23,759 --> 01:25:26,193
...with this whole
medical system?

1286
01:25:29,664 --> 01:25:31,598
Hey, I'll race ya!

1287
01:25:31,666 --> 01:25:35,659
We gave them our son.
We gave them our trust.

1288
01:25:35,737 --> 01:25:38,570
We damn near had
to give 'em our home.

1289
01:25:38,640 --> 01:25:42,701
But instead of giving us
the simplest information...

1290
01:25:42,778 --> 01:25:46,544
...they abused Robbie, and
they almost destroyed us all.

1291
01:25:46,615 --> 01:25:52,451
- Yea, I won! I won!
- Not that any of'em will ever ask...

1292
01:25:52,521 --> 01:25:57,424
...but I wonder if they have
any idea of the pain they caused.

1293
01:25:57,492 --> 01:25:59,653
And I wonder if someday
I'm gonna be able to find...

1294
01:25:59,728 --> 01:26:03,220
...in my heart a way
to get past the anger...

1295
01:26:03,298 --> 01:26:05,357
...and feel forgiveness.

1296
01:26:07,302 --> 01:26:11,739
I don't know, Dave.
I don't know.

1297
01:26:15,644 --> 01:26:18,078
- Hello?
- Hi, it's me.

1298
01:26:18,146 --> 01:26:21,309
- Is everything okay?
- Yeah, we're fine.

1299
01:26:24,753 --> 01:26:28,052
- How's Robbie doing?
- Well...

1300
01:26:30,826 --> 01:26:34,853
...he's almost
our old kid again.

1301
01:26:34,930 --> 01:26:37,626
I think he's comin' back
to us, Dave.

1302
01:26:37,699 --> 01:26:39,997
Ohh.

1303
01:26:40,068 --> 01:26:42,536
- Thank God.
- [Laughs]

1304
01:26:42,604 --> 01:26:45,402
I miss you so much.

1305
01:26:45,474 --> 01:26:48,170
I miss you too.

1306
01:26:48,243 --> 01:26:50,211
I miss us.

1307
01:26:52,214 --> 01:26:54,512
Do you miss us?

1308
01:26:54,583 --> 01:26:57,984
Oh, boy, do I miss us.

1309
01:26:58,053 --> 01:26:59,987
[Laughs]

1310
01:27:02,357 --> 01:27:05,019
Tell me.

1311
01:27:05,093 --> 01:27:09,427
- Dave, we're in a convent here.
- [Laughing]

1312
01:27:09,498 --> 01:27:12,433
Give the nuns something
to remember you by. [Laughing]

1313
01:27:12,501 --> 01:27:14,435
[Laughing]

1314
01:27:16,938 --> 01:27:19,372
[People Cheering]

1315
01:27:19,441 --> 01:27:23,571
